@flouthoc @cevich PTAL


There are multiple ways to fix this
 - do not use ssh, use `sudo -E` instead;
 - write/source a file with all environment variables that needs to be passed;
 - add a bunch of `export VAR=$VALUE` to ssh invocation, before test.sh (e.g. `export STORAGE_DRIVER=$STORAGE_DRIVER; $GOSRC/$SCRIPT_BASE/test.sh`;
 - configure ssh AND sshd to send and accept extra env vars (`SendEnv` for ssh, `AcceptEnv` for sshd).
